OL,3,CSkipper's near miss after boat
OL,4,Ccapsizes near Exmouth
OL,6,FThe end of the net was full of sand,
OL,7,Fmud and fish. Once it was lifted out
OL,8,Fthe water, it swung away from vessel's
OL,9,Fside causing it to capsize.
OL,11,FThe skipper did not have time to raise
OL,12,Fthe alarm before entering the water.
OL,14,FHowever they were wearing a lifejacket
OL,15,Ffitted with a personal locator beacon
OL,16,Fand managed to swim to the vessel's
OL,17,Fliferaft, which had floated free.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
